-- Toyota May Build Prius Lithium-Ion Battery Factory in Japan, Yomiuri Says
-- B y   K a z u y o   S a w a
-- 2010-10-21T22:10:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/toyota-may-build-lithium-ion-plant-in-japan-yomiuri-says.html
Toyota Motor Corp. is considering
building a factory in Japan to produce lithium-ion batteries for
use in Prius hybrid vehicles, the Yomiuri newspaper reported,
without saying where it obtained the information.  The batteries will be smaller and more powerful than
conventional nickel-metal hydride cells. Production may begin as
early as 2014, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kazuyo Sawa in Tokyo at 
